{"questionId":"13337","questionHtml":"<p>Find the Cartesian equation of the plane containing P, Q and R.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>for example</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\overrightarrow {{\\text{PQ}}} = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  { - 1} \\\\   { - 5} \\\\   8  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>PQ</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>→</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>5</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>8</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\overrightarrow {{\\text{PR}}} = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  1 \\\\   { - 6} \\\\   3  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>PR</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>→</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>6</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\overrightarrow {{\\text{PQ}}}&nbsp; \\times \\overrightarrow {{\\text{PR}}} \">\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>PQ</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>→</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>PR</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>→</mo>\n  </mover>\n</math></span> = 33<em><strong>i</strong></em> + 11<em><strong>j</strong></em> + 11<em><strong>k&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>r.n</strong></em> = <em><strong>a.n</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"33x + 11y + 11z = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  0 \\\\   1 \\\\   1  \\end{array}} \\right) \\cdot \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {33} \\\\   {11} \\\\   {11}  \\end{array}} \\right) = 22\">\n  <mn>33</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>11</mn>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>11</mn>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>⋅</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>33</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>11</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>11</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>22</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow 3x + y + z = 2\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;or equivalent&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>assume plane can be written as&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"ax + by + cz = 1\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>substituting each set of coordinates gives the system of equations:</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a + 6b - 7c = 1\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>7</mn>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0a + b + c = 1\">\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2a + 0b - 4c = 1\">\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>solving by GDC&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a = \\frac{3}{2}\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b = \\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"C = \\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow \\frac{3}{2}x + \\frac{1}{2}y + \\frac{1}{2}z = 1\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;or equivalent</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13337","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ2.H_11a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the Cartesian equation of the plane containing P, Q and R.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.17—Vector equations of a plane","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.18—Intersections of lines & planes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}